  "body": "\r\nThis is a very much needed future.\r\n\r\nA flag to confirm if I want to update the old version to newest when launching it would be very useful to avoid update issues creeping when process restarts etc.\r\n\r\nReason being that automated scripts can restart process without the issue of updating to latest release when not knowing if latest release is buggy or safe. \r\n\r\nI rather experiment with latest release on a different non production system before safely doing it on heavily loaded production systems. \r\n\r\nIntroduce Parameter:\r\n\r\n  --update=yes or no  \r\n    \r\n   on the prysm.sh command line.",
