    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "One workaround is to set the environment variable for the version you wish to use.\r\n\r\n```\r\nUSE_PRYSM_VERSION=v1.3.0 ./prysm.sh validator --version\r\n\r\n# Prints the following\r\nvalidator version Prysm/v1.3.0/ad9cd1933ae08ff2b6c083bda2993a50fa01d0b5. Built at: 2021-02-22 20:35:16+00:00\r\n```\r\nThis always uses version v1.3.0, even if that is not the \"latest\" release.",
